        <Parent_String>organic pigment [300013120], pigment by composition or origin [300013110], pigments [300013109], colorant (material) [300013026], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pigments comprising carbon-based molecules manufactured from petroleum compounds, acids, and other chemicals, usually under intense heat or pressure. Many are not sufficient for permanent painting. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047814/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種由中間體製造的顏料，中間體相對地是取自煤焦油或其它形式的石油或碳經蒸餾而成的原料。這些進程可說是十九世紀下半葉有機化學發展的副產品，而有機化學的發展始於西元1856年發現佩金苯胺紫。然而，合成有機顏料中很多色彩不夠持久，造成此詞彙帶有貶抑。煤焦顏料是合成有機顏料頗過時的名稱。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
